						<summary>

						<p>On the seventh pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Tyāgarāja shrine in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Parāntaka I. Year 19: 925-26 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of 10 <hi rend="italic">poṉ</hi> left in the hands of the temple authorities and 90 sheep left under the care of the temple shepherds, by Iḍaiyaṉ Kiḻaṅgāri, for burning two perpetual lamps to the deity Tirumaṟaikkāṭṭu Āḻvār.</p>						

						</summary>
